"1514","1501":"1501","abt 1524":"circa 1524","1465":"1465","about 1501":"circa 1501","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","14 December 1528":"14 december 1528","15 August 1514":"15 augustus 1514","1528":"1528","1538":"1538","1505":"1505","1603":"1603","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England"},"en":{"about 1501–1536":"about 1501–1536","1495–Male":"1495–Deceased","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1505–Female":"1505–Deceased","1528–1562":"1528–1562","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495":"1495","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","abt 1524":"about 1524","1465":"1465","about 1501":"about 1501","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","14 December 1528":"14 December 1528","15 August 1514":"15 August 1514","1528":"1528","1538":"1538","1505":"1505","1603":"1603","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Redman","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name from Middle English <i>red</i> (Old English <i>hrēod</i>) ‘reed’ + <i>-man</i>, presumably for a thatcher or reed-cutter. Compare   Reeder  .","English: in southeastern England sometimes a topographic name perhaps for someone who lived by a clearing, from Middle English <i>rede</i> (Old English <i>rēod</i>, <i>rȳd</i>) ‘clearing’ + <i>man</i>.","English: habitational name from Redmain (Cumberland), from Old English <i>rēad</i> ‘red’ + an uncertain second element, perhaps a dialect form of <i>man</i> ‘cairn’."],"variants":[{"name":"Reeder","meanings":["English: occupational name for someone who used reeds as a roofing material (a thatcher), a derivative of Middle English <i>rede</i> ‘reed’ + <i>-er</i>. Compare   Reed   and   Redman  .","English: topographic name for someone who lived by a clearing, a derivative of Middle English <i>rede</i>, <i>ride</i>, <i>rude</i> ‘clearing’ (see   Reed  ) + <i>-er</i>, synonymous and interchangeable with <i>atte Rede</i>, <i>atte Rude</i> ‘at the clearing’. This type of name, composed of a topographic term + <i>-er</i>, is common in Kent, Surrey and Sussex, and it is also found in Essex.","Dutch and German: variant of   Reder   3."]},{"name":"Redhead","meanings":["English:","nickname for someone with red hair, from Middle English <i>red</i> ‘red’ + <i>he(ve)d</i> ‘head’. Compare   Redman  .","habitational name from an unidentified place in northern England called <i>Redhead</i>, probably meaning ‘red headland’."]},{"name":"Rodman","meanings":["English: occupational name for a thatcher or reed-cutter, from Southwest Middle English <i>rod(e)</i>, <i>rud(e)</i> (Old English <i>hrēod</i>) ‘reed’ + <i>-man</i>. Synonymous with   Redman   1.","English: topographic name for someone who lived at a clearing, from Middle English <i>rode</i> (Old English <i>rodu</i>) or Southwest Middle English <i>rude</i> (Old English <i>rȳde</i>) ‘clearing’ + <i>man</i>. See   Redman   2.","Americanized form of German <b>Rodmann</b>: variant of <b>Rodemann</b> (see   Rodeman  )."]}]},{"name":"Edwin","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old English personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>wine</i> ‘friend’. It was borne by a 7th-century king of Northumbria, who was converted to Christianity by  St Paulinus  and was killed in battle against pagan forces, a combination of circumstances which led to his being venerated as a martyr. The name occurs occasionally from the mid 16th century, but in modern use it is largely the result of a 19th-century revival."],"variants":[{"name":"Edwyn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Edwin ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Edwin Redman was born about 1501, in Northill, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Redman, was 37 and his mother, Anne Scrope, was 33. He married Lola Ann Wilhoit about 1524, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1536, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"about 1501–1536":"umbes 1501–1536","1495–Male":"1495–Surnud","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1505–Female":"1505–Surnud","1528–1562":"1528–1562","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495":"1495","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","abt 1524":"umbes 1524","1465":"1465","about 1501":"umbes 1501","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","14 December 1528":"14. detsember 1528","15 August 1514":"15. august 1514","1528":"1528","1538":"1538","1505":"1505","1603":"1603","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1501–1536":"noin 1501–1536","1495–Male":"1495–Kuollut","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1505–Female":"1505–Kuollut","1528–1562":"1528–1562","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495":"1495","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","abt 1524":"noin 1524","1465":"1465","about 1501":"noin 1501","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","14 December 1528":"14. joulukuuta 1528","15 August 1514":"15. elokuuta 1514","1528":"1528","1538":"1538","1505":"1505","1603":"1603","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1501–1536":"environ 1501–1536","1495–Male":"1495–Décédé","1496–16